      <p>This category includes working breeds such as collies, huskies, and St. Bernards.</p>
      <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage"/>
        <a name="id2283269"/>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">other</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals52"/>
        <p><span class="strong"><strong>Carrying Capacity:</strong></span> A light load for a <a href="ch73s16.html#MonstersAnimals51">riding dog</a> is up to 100 pounds; a medium load, 101-200 pounds; and a heavy load, 201-300 pounds. A <a href="ch73s16.html#MonstersAnimals51">riding dog</a> can drag 1,500 pounds.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id2283319"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals53"/>
        <p>If trained for war, these animals can make trip attacks just as <a href="ch73s47.html#MonstersAnimals183">wolves</a> do (see the <a href="ch73s47.html#MonstersAnimals183">Wolf</a> entry). A <a href="ch73s16.html#MonstersAnimals51">riding dog</a> can fight while carrying a rider, but the rider cannot also attack unless he or she succeeds on a <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills243">Ride</a> check.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2283380"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals54"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> <a href="ch73s16.html#MonstersAnimals51">Riding dogs</a> have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills192">Jump</a> checks. *<a href="ch73s16.html#MonstersAnimals51">Riding dogs</a> have a +4 racial bonus on <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills303">Survival</a> checks when tracking by scent.</p>
